Class AppInterfaceCommandInvocationException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.java.AppInterfaceCommandException
          • com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.java.AppInterfaceCommandInvocationException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AppInterfaceCommandInvocationException
extends AppInterfaceCommandException

    Checked exceptions of type AppInterfaceCommandInvocationException are thrown by an AppInterfaceCommand command bean to signal function invocation or processing errors that prevented its interface function from completing an execution request.

    The bean's AppInterfaceCommand.execute() method is arranged to raise such exceptions as appropriate, at which time the underlying exception identifying the error can be retrieved with Throwable.getCause().
